    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with tin foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork</strong> <strong>shoulder </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Chop most of your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks (save some for a garnish!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is lightly browned, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> fish sauce</strong>,<strong> tamarind paste </strong>and <strong>garam masala</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chopped coconut </strong>with your <strong>ginger paste </strong>and<strong> ketjap manis</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 25 min \u2013 this is your <strong>curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the curry has had 25 min, reboil a kettle</p><p>Remove the curry from the oven and add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong>, then give it a good mix up and return the dish to oven, covered, and cook for 30 min or until the pork is tender and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Northern Thai-inspired pork & squash curry</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p><p>Once the curry<strong> </strong>is ready, remove the dish from the oven and add the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then set aside for 2-3 min for the flavours to develop</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/northern-thai-inspired-pork-and-squash-curry-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Northern Thai-inspired pork & squash curry</strong> with the <strong>rice </strong>to the side</p><p>For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
